Our client is a high profile, CNC Engineering business, specializing in the
manufacture, assembly and testing of fully integrated parts for aerospace and
naval defense contacts.

Due to growth within the business, we are now looking to add an experienced
CNC Programmer to the team. Working in the comfort of a modern facility,
furnished with only the very best, state of the art machines and software, you
will be required to create complex programs for 3, 4 and 5 axis mills.

Ideally the successful candidate will be able to demonstrate most or all of
the following selection criteria. However candidates from a similar background
with similar skill sets are also strongly encouraged to apply:

  * Minimum 3 years experience in a similar role 
  * Ideally you will be proficient with Mastercam and/or Catia programming software. 
  * The ability to read and understand technical engineering drawings & specifications 
  * Possess an understanding of geometric dimensioning and tolerancing principles. 
  * Use of measuring equipment including Vernier’s, Micrometers etc. 
  * Previous hands on CNC milling and a familiarity with 5 axis machines would be highly regarded. 

On offer to the successful applicant is an attractive base salary and the
opportunity to work on complex and diverse solutions, within a highly
respected business.

If the above sounds like you and you are looking for an opportunity to work in
a terrific environment with an “employer of choice”, where quality is
paramount, then please Apply Now or call Andrew Witt on [ 0418 796 262
](tel:0418 796 262) for a confidential discussion.

